    "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nCuTeDSL (Python) port of CUTLASS Example 54 — a Hopper (SM90) FP8 warp-specialized GEMM with the 2xAcc (double accumulation) technique for improved FP8 numerical accuracy.\r\n\r\n### What is 2xAcc?\r\n\r\nFP8 has limited dynamic range, so naively accumulating many FP8 MMA products into a single Float32 accumulator can lose precision. The 2xAcc technique maintains two register accumulators inside the mainloop:\r\n\r\n- `accum_temp`: WGMMA writes directly into this temporary accumulator\r\n- `accumulators`: The main accumulator that collects promoted partial results\r\n\r\nEvery `mma_promotion_interval` MMA instructions (default 4), `accum_temp` is promoted (element-wise added) into `accumulators`, then zeroed for the next batch. This bounds the number of low-precision products accumulated before promotion to full precision.\r\n\r\nThe C++ reference for this algorithm is in:\r\n\r\n- `fp8_accumulation.hpp` — `GmmaFP8Accumulation` class\r\n- `sm90_mma_tma_gmma_ss_warpspecialized_fp8.hpp` — mainloop integration\r\n\r\n### Features\r\n\r\n- FP8 E4M3FN inputs (k-major) with Float32 accumulation\r\n- 2xAcc mainloop with configurable `--mma_promotion_interval`\r\n- Scalar `scale_a` / `scale_b` applied in the epilogue: `D = scale_a * scale_b * (A @ B)`\r\n- TMA loads with multicast, warp specialization (DMA + MMA warp groups)\r\n- Persistent tile scheduling (`StaticPersistentTileScheduler`)\r\n- Configurable output dtype (`Float16`, `Float32`, `Float8E4M3FN`)\r\n- Reference validation and benchmarking harness\r\n\r\n### New files\r\n\r\n- `examples/python/CuTeDSL/hopper/dense_gemm_fp8_2xacc.py` — kernel implementation (based on `dense_gemm_persistent.py` with the mainloop replaced by the 2xAcc algorithm)\r\n- `test/examples/CuTeDSL/hopper/test_dense_gemm_fp8_2xacc.py` — pytest test suite (L0 compile, L1 correctness, benchmarks)\r\n\r\n### Usage\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n```bash\r\n# Basic run with reference check\r\npython examples/python/CuTeDSL/hopper/dense_gemm_fp8_2xacc.py \\\r\n  --mnkl 2048,2048,2048,1 --tile_shape_mn 128,128 \\\r\n  --cluster_shape_mn 1,2 --mma_promotion_interval 4\r\n                                                                                                                                                                                    \r\n# With non-trivial scale factors:\r\npython examples/python/CuTeDSL/hopper/dense_gemm_fp8_2xacc.py \\\r\n    --mnkl 2048,2048,2048,1 --scale_a 0.5 --scale_b 2.0                                                                                     \r\n                                                            \r\n# Benchmark (cold L2, 100 iterations):                                                                                                      \r\n python examples/python/CuTeDSL/hopper/dense_gemm_fp8_2xacc.py \\\r\n    --mnkl 8192,8192,4096,1 --tile_shape_mn 128,256 --cluster_shape_mn 2,2 \\                                                                \r\n    --warmup_iterations 20 --iterations 100 --skip_ref_check --use_cold_l2                                                                  \r\n```\r\n\r\n###  Constraints                                                                                                                                                                                  \r\n  - Hopper (SM90) only                                                                                                                      \r\n  - FP8 E4M3FN inputs, k-major layout only                  \r\n  - Output dtype: Float16, Float32, or Float8E4M3FN\r\n  - CTA tile M: 64/128, N: 64/128/256                                                                                                       \r\n  - Cluster M/N must be a power of 2; total cluster size ≤ 4\r\n  - mma_promotion_interval must be a multiple of num_k_blocks (typically 4)                                                                 \r\n  - K dimension must be aligned to 16 FP8 elements (16 bytes)                                                                               \r\n   \r\n### Test plan                                                                                                                                                                                             \r\n  Run from the cutlass repo root:\r\n```bash\r\n  # All correctness tests (L0 compile + L1 reference check):                                                                                \r\n  python -m pytest test/examples/CuTeDSL/hopper/test_dense_gemm_fp8_2xacc.py --target-cc 90 -v\r\n                                                                                                                                            \r\n  # L0 only (compile + single execution, no reference check — faster):\r\n  python -m pytest test/examples/CuTeDSL/hopper/test_dense_gemm_fp8_2xacc.py --target-cc 90 -m L0 -v                                        \r\n                                                                                                                                            \r\n  # L1 only (full numerical validation vs torch.einsum):\r\n  python -m pytest test/examples/CuTeDSL/hopper/test_dense_gemm_fp8_2xacc.py --target-cc 90 -m L1 -v                                        \r\n                                                                                                                                            \r\n  # Benchmarks (prints µs and TFLOPS per config):\r\n  python -m pytest test/examples/CuTeDSL/hopper/test_dense_gemm_fp8_2xacc.py --target-cc 90 -m bench -s -v                                  \r\n```\r\n                                                                                                                        \r\n  ###  Coverage:\r\n  - All tile shapes: (64,64), (128,64), (128,128), (128,256)                                                                                \r\n  - All cluster shapes: (1,1), (2,1), (1,2), (2,2)          \r\n  - All output dtypes: Float16, Float32, Float8E4M3FN\r\n  - mma_promotion_interval: 4, 8, 16                                                                                                        \r\n  - Non-trivial scale factors (scale_a=0.5/2.0, scale_b=2.0/0.5, etc.)\r\n  - Batched GEMM (L=2, L=4)\r\n \r\n<img width=\"528\" height=\"240\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/fc31a765-c8f5-406a-bf97-fe56ceae435f\" />\r\n\r\n                                                                                  \r\n                                                               ",
